      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Natural rights theorists argue that the right to speak is inherent to human personhood, not a privilege granted by the state, making its application to the borderless internet even more critical. The internet functions as a global public square, a decentralized commons where traditional state control is structurally impossible, unlike physical town squares or broadcast media. To regulate it is to attempt to impose parochial, centralized authority onto a fundamentally ungovernable, universal sphere of human discourse.",
